d London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/97781-pod-save-america-and-lovett-or-leave-it-are-coming-to-london-in-january-heres-how-to-get-tickets/|title=Pod Save America and Lovett or Leave It are coming to London in January, here's how to get tickets|date=December 1, 2017|work=The List|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Content==\nThe podcast typically covers recent news items relating to politics, including the Trump administration, the US government and the Democratic Party, as well as progressive grassroots activism.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/mar/19/the-week-in-radio-pod-save-america-the-long-view-podcast|title=The week in radio: Pod Save America; The Long View|last=Sawyer|first=Miranda|date=March 19, 2017|work=The Observer|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\nThe show typically features interviews with politicians, activists and journalists, including Obama's last interview as president.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/jan/26/pod-save-america-the-podcast-that-won-obamas-last-interview|title=Pod Save America \u2013 the podcast that won Obama's last interview|last=Verdier|first=Hannah|date=January 26, 2017|work=The Guardian|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Other guests have included [[Hillary Clinton]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/hillary-clinton-trump-clear-present-threat-pod-save-america-podcast-interview-a7943726.html|title=Hillary Clinton says Donald Trump 'is a clear and present danger to America'|date=September 12, 2017|work=The Independent|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> and senators [[Bernie Sanders]], [[Elizabeth Warren]], [[Cory Booker]], [[Kamala Harris]], and [[Chris Murphy (Connecticut politician)|Chris Murphy]]. They have interviewed several current and former [[2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries|2020 Democratic Presidential candidates]], including Sanders, Booker, Harris, [[Beto O'Rourke]], [[Andrew Yang]], [[Pete Buttigieg]], [[Marianne Williamson]], and [[Amy Klobuchar]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://crooked.com/podcast-series/pod-save-america/|title=Pod Save America Archives|website=Crooked Media|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-24}}</ref>. Guests are often referred to as \"friends of the pod\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.vice.com/en_ca/article/a3jadk/podcasts-are-becoming-the-lefts-right-wing-talk-radio|title=Podcasts are becoming the left's right-wing talk radio|work=VICE News|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pod Save America (30363).jpg|thumb|Favreau, Vietor, and guest [[Seth Meyers]] at a live taping at [[Radio City Music Hall]]]]\n\n== Reception ==\nThe show averages more than 1.5 million listeners an episode, and had been downloaded more than 120 million times by November 2017.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' described the podcast as \"one of the big breakout hits of the nascent resistance movement\",<ref name=\":1\" /> and \"the left's answer to conservative talk radio... with a shoestring budget and no organizational backing, its hosts seem to have created something that liberals have spent almost two decades, and hundreds of millions of dollars, futilely searching for\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' called it \"one of the nation's most popular podcasts\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sfchronicle.com/politics/article/Pod-Save-America-about-to-take-its-next-step-12418780.php|title='Pod Save America' about to take its next step|work=San Francisco Chronicle|access-date=January 3, 2018}}</ref> ''[[GQ]]'' called it one of the \"most popular strategies for coping with the looming death of the republic\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/pod-save-america-colbert|title=The 'Pod Save America' Guys Gave Donald Trump His Best, Weirdest Nickname Yet|last=Willis|first=Jay|date=April 6, 2017|work=GQ|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n''[[Newsweek]]'' wrote that the show's hosts \"do something far more rare [than political analysis], which is to make politics entertaining and even fun, without ever downplaying what they see as the threat posed to American democracy by the man elected to defend it.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsweek.com/crooked-media-fights-trump-pod-save-america-jon-favreau-jon-lovett-tommy-570695|title=How the Crooked Media trio is taking on Donald Trump with \"Pod Save America\"|date=March 26, 2017|work=Newsweek|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Pod Save the World]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://crooked.com/podcast-series/pod-save-america/}}\n\n{{Crooked Media}}\n\n[[Category:2017 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Audio podcasts]]\n[[Category:Political podcasts]]\n[[Category:Crooked Media]]\n", "name_user": "71.82.77.112", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pod_Save_America"}
